                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d135">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">762.94/58: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-25T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 25, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 25—9:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>111. An usually very dependable source claims that a secret German-Japanese
                    military alliance has just been concluded and that 70 Japanese officers are
                    coming to Germany for liaison purposes.</p>
                <p>It will take some time to reach conclusions as to truth of this statement here,
                    so submit it with all reserve.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodd</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
